# Testing conventions

This project has three Vitest projects (see `apps/mind-map-sv/vite.config.ts`):

| Project | Env | Files | Use for |
|---|---|---|---|
| `server` | node | `**/*.spec.ts`, `**/*.test.ts` (non-svelte) | pure logic, no DOM |
| `client` | browser (chromium) | `**/*.svelte.{spec,test}.ts` | component-level tests needing real DOM |
| `storybook` | browser (chromium) | every `*.stories.svelte` `play` | scenario / behavior tests |

Plus Playwright for E2E (`apps/mind-map-sv/e2e/*.test.ts`) — full app flow only.

## Decision tree for "where does this test go?"

1. Pure function (no DOM, no Svelte)? → unit spec colocated with the source.
2. Component behavior, gesture, or visual scenario? → Storybook story with `play`.
3. Persistence, routing, or multi-page flow? → Playwright e2e.
4. CSS regression / visual diff? → already covered by Chromatic on every story.

When in doubt, write the unit spec first; reach for Storybook only when the
behavior genuinely involves the DOM (gestures, layout measurement, focus).

## Unit spec template

```ts
import { describe, it, expect } from 'vitest';
import { foo } from './foo';

describe('foo', () => {
  describe('when given empty input', () => {
    it('returns the empty fallback', () => {
      expect(foo([])).toEqual([]);
    });
  });
  // ... more cases
});
```

Pattern after `Multigraph/lib/graphMath.spec.ts`.

## Story `play` template

```svelte
<Story
  name="UserPinsANode"
  args={{ nodes: NODES.slice(0, 3) }}
  play={async ({ canvasElement }) => {
    const wrapper = canvasElement.querySelector('[data-testid="stage-callbacks"]') as HTMLElement;
    expect(wrapper).toBeInTheDocument();
    // synthesize gesture, wait for layout, assert on data-* attribute
  }}
/>
```

Pattern after `Multigraph/Stage.stories.svelte`. Always:
- Name stories like a sentence describing the user behavior tested
- Assert on `data-*` attributes from the harness, not on internal component state
- Use `await waitForLayout()` and `await sleep()` from the existing helpers

## Use the harness, don't replace it

`StageHarness.svelte` exposes Stage's callback firings as `data-last-*`
attributes. New stage-related stories must assert via the harness. If you need
a new callback exposed, add a `data-last-...` attribute to the harness — don't
fork it.

## Test fixtures

Use `apps/mind-map-sv/src/lib/components/ui/Multigraph/lib/testFixtures.ts`
to build graph data. Don't hand-roll inline node/edge arrays in every test —
extend the fixtures helper instead.

## Do not test implementation details

- Don't assert on private state.
- Don't snapshot whole DOM trees (Chromatic handles visual regression).
- Do assert on the user-visible outcome and on the public callback contract.

## Always run tests before claiming done

```bash
pnpm --filter mind-map-sv test:unit -- --run
```

If you touched anything visible, also confirm Storybook builds:

```bash
pnpm --filter mind-map-sv build-storybook
```
